pullRequest.body:
We define the property `IsConjRoot K x y` as two elements having the same minimal polynomial over `K`. We show that it is equivalent to the existence of an algebra equivalence `œÉ : L ‚âÉ‚Çê[K] L` such that `y = œÉ x`. We also show that if `x` is a separable element over `K` and the minimal polynomial of `x` splits in `L`, then `x` is not in the `K` iff there exists a different conjugate root of `x` in `L` over `K`. Most of the properties have a similar version already proved in Mathlib.

---

```suggestion
Given two elements `x` and `y` of some `K`-algebra, these two elements are *conjugate roots* over `K`
if they have the same minimal polynomial over `K`.
```
Thank you!

```suggestion
We say that `y` is a conjugate root of `x` over `K` if the minimal polynomial of `x` is the
same as the minimal polynomial of `y`.
-/
def IsConjRoot (x y : A) : Prop := (minpoly R x) = (minpoly R y)
```
To match the module docstring...

Please also update below.
Thank you! Now all of the variables are `x` and `y` instead of `x` and `x'`.

These parentheses can be dropped, right?
```suggestion
def IsConjRoot (x y : A) : Prop := minpoly R x = minpoly R y
```
Thanks!
Maybe add a `@[simp]`-tagged `iff` version for this, like you did for `isConjRoot_zero_iff_eq_zero`?
Thank you! Added.
Could you also add the symmetric version as `@[simp]` lemma, stating `IsConjRoot K x 0 ‚Üî x = 0`?
Thank you! Added.
[#6718](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/6718/files#r1816397133) needs the Setoid so you may as well add it here.
Added. Thank you!
Looks like this is only used much later. Can you move it down?
Moved. Thank you!

```suggestion
@[trans] theorem trans {x y y': A} (h‚ÇÅ : IsConjRoot R x y) (h‚ÇÇ : IsConjRoot R y y') :
```
Thanks!

```suggestion
@[refl] theorem refl {x : A} : IsConjRoot R x x := rfl
```
Thank you!

```suggestion
@[symm] theorem symm {x y : A} (h : IsConjRoot R x y) : IsConjRoot R y x := Eq.symm h
```
Thank you!

```suggestion
variable {R K L S A B : Type*} [CommRing R] [CommRing S] [Ring A] [Ring B] [Field K] [Field L]
```
Thanks!

```lean
theorem isConjRoot_iff_orbitRel [Normal K L] {x y : L} :
    IsConjRoot K x y ‚Üî MulAction.orbitRel (L ‚âÉ‚Çê[K] L) L y x :=
  isConjRoot_iff_exists_algEquiv
```
It might be better to exchange `x` and `y` to match `orbitRel`.
Thanks! I'll exchange `x` and `y` and add this `isConjRoot_iff_orbitRel`.

```suggestion
* Move `IsConjRoot` to earlier files and refactor the theorems in field theory using `IsConjRoot`.
```

```suggestion
The setoid structure on `A` defined by the equivalence relation of `IsConjRoot R ¬∑ ¬∑`.
-/

```
